{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "9d484e9d-95be-4ca3-ae0f-95f8aa22d7a0",
    "name": "CrownBid Auth API",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "description": "Auth-2 — flujo real: **personas + clientes + cliente_credenciales**, JWT **stateless** (sin `revoked_tokens`), logout **204 sin escritura en BD**.\n\n**Antes de probar:** ejecutar `database/cliente_credenciales.sql` en SQL Server; datos mínimos en `paises` (p. ej. `countryId` 1); SMTP o modo dev (mock en consola con contraseña temporal).\n\n**Variables:**\n- `registerEmail` / `loginEmail`: mismo usuario.\n- `registerDocumentNumber`: documento único por corrida (cambiar si ya existe).\n- `temporaryPassword`: tras registro, correo o log `[email mock]` en dev.\n- `newPassword`: ≥8 caracteres, al menos **una mayúscula** y **una minúscula** (dígito opcional).\n\n**Orden sugerido:** Register success → copiar temp password → Login first login → Change initial password → Login after change (opcional, actualiza token) → Users me → Logout.\n\n**Deshabilitado (501):** forgot-password, reset-password (ítems al final)."
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:3000" },
    { "key": "registerEmail", "value": "nasser.phase2.postman@example.com" },
    { "key": "loginEmail", "value": "nasser.phase2.postman@example.com" },
    { "key": "registerDocumentNumber", "value": "12345678" },
    { "key": "temporaryPassword", "value": "" },
    { "key": "newPassword", "value": "NuevaPasswordAb" },
    { "key": "accessTokenInitial", "value": "" },
    { "key": "accessToken", "value": "" }
  ],
